# Cline Rules — Advanced Playwright Framework

## Quality Gates
Run these in order after EVERY code change. Do not mark a task done until all 4 pass:

```bash
npm run typecheck                        # 1. Zero TypeScript errors
npm run lint                             # 2. Zero ESLint errors
npm run format:check                     # 3. All files formatted (npm run format to fix)
npx playwright test --grep @smoke        # 4. Smoke suite green
```

## Project Layout
```
src/pages/        → Page Object classes (one per page, extend BasePage)
src/fixtures/     → Custom Playwright fixtures (test-base.ts)
src/tests/        → Spec files organized by feature
src/testdata/     → JSON · CSV · XLSX · TypeScript interfaces
src/utils/        → logger · reporter · file reader · data factory
src/config/       → Environment URL mapping
rules/            → Quality gate definitions (source of truth)
```

## Code Rules

### Locators — always arrow functions
```typescript
loginBtn = () => this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Login' });
```

### Tests — always tagged
```typescript
test('@smoke @P0 should login successfully', async ({ loginPage }) => { ... });
```

### Logger — always scoped
```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@utils/logger';
const log = createLogger('LoginPage');
```

### Imports — always use path aliases
```typescript
import { LoginPage } from '@pages/LoginPage';
import { test }      from '@fixtures/test-base';
import logger        from '@utils/logger';
```

## Forbidden
- `as any` or `// @ts-ignore` without a written reason
- Inline `// eslint-disable` without a comment
- Tests without tags
- Locators as class properties (stale element risk)
- Files outside the correct `src/` subfolder
- Committing when typecheck / lint / format:check fails
